article.headline: Valparaiso 67, Chicago State 64
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Shawn Huff scored 17 points and grabbed six rebounds to lead Valparaiso to a 67-64 victory over Chicago State on Saturday. Samuel Haanpaa added 14 points and Brandon McPherson had 13 points for the Crusaders (5-8) who won for the second time in the last 10 games. Royce Parran led Chicago State (5-12) with 19 points on 6-of-9 shooting. Michael Henderson had 14 points and John Cantrell came off the bench to score 10 points for Chicago State. The Cougars built their lead to 11 points with 3:28 left in the first half and led 34-33 at halftime. The Crusaders outshot the Cougars in the second half and led by nine points with 2:37 remaining. Chicago State was held to 8-of-21 (38 percent) shooting in the second half. Valparaiso held a 32-27 rebounding edge, but was outscored in the paint 22-18.
